abstract: After a shrine for her daughter was removed, Evelyn Rodriguez confronted a nearby driver, a friend said. They argued. The driver sped off and ran her over.
snippet: After a shrine for her daughter was removed, Evelyn Rodriguez confronted a nearby driver, a friend said. They argued. The driver sped off and ran her over.
lead_paragraph: A day later on Long Island, the cruel symmetry of tragedy was still too much for family, friends and officials to comprehend.

abstract: Ms. Rodriguez, who was a vocal advocate for victims of MS-13 gang members, attended the State of the Union address in January at President Trump’s invitation.
snippet: Ms. Rodriguez, who was a vocal advocate for victims of MS-13 gang members, attended the State of the Union address in January at President Trump’s invitation.
lead_paragraph: Evelyn Rodriguez, who became a vocal advocate for victims of gang violence after members of the transnational gang MS-13 were charged with killing her 16-year-old daughter, died after being struck by an S.U.V. on Friday — just before a memorial service for the second anniversary of her daughter’s death.

abstract: The morning after his decisive primary win, Gov. Andrew Cuomo all but dismissed the idea that he had been threatened by an insurgent wave.
snippet: The morning after his decisive primary win, Gov. Andrew Cuomo all but dismissed the idea that he had been threatened by an insurgent wave.
lead_paragraph: Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo was the epitome of the very establishment the Democratic left has been frothing against: He raised big checks from big corporate powers. He was a dynastic candidate seeking a third term. He talked about capping taxes and constraining spending.

abstract: Svyatoslav I. Vakarchuk, Ukraine’s favorite musician, sang the protest anthems for two popular uprisings and is now considering a run for president.
snippet: Svyatoslav I. Vakarchuk, Ukraine’s favorite musician, sang the protest anthems for two popular uprisings and is now considering a run for president.
lead_paragraph: KIEV, Ukraine — In the midst of Ukraine’s revolution, the pop singer Svyatoslav I. Vakarchuk jumped onto a stage before almost a quarter of a million protesters. With steam billowing from his mouth in the frigid air, he clenched a microphone wrapped in Ukraine’s blue and yellow flag and sang to his country: “My darling! Rise up my dear! Wake up!”

abstract: The reigning Olympic champion has won an unheard-of eight straight marathons. Can he capture the world record Sunday in Berlin?
snippet: The reigning Olympic champion has won an unheard-of eight straight marathons. Can he capture the world record Sunday in Berlin?
lead_paragraph: BERLIN — Eliud Kipchoge, the most decorated marathoner on the planet, is a man of immense self-discipline. He rolls out of bed at 5 a.m. for his morning runs. He splits his time between his home in Eldoret, Kenya, where he lives with his wife and three children, and a training camp up in the hills, 8,000 feet above sea level, where he shares chores with teammates.

abstract: Six Democrats who collaborated with Republicans as part of the disbanded Independent Democratic Conference lost their primary bids to challengers.
snippet: Six Democrats who collaborated with Republicans as part of the disbanded Independent Democratic Conference lost their primary bids to challengers.
lead_paragraph: Years of anger at a group of Democratic state senators who had collaborated with Republicans boiled over on Thursday, as primary voters ousted nearly all of them in favor of challengers who had called them traitors and sham progressives.

headline_main: Democratic Insurgents Topple 6 New York Senate Incumbents
headline_print_headline: Insurgents Unseat Bloc of G.O.P.-Leaning Democrats in State Senate

abstract: Gov. Andrew Cuomo sought to use the power of incumbency and a huge fund-raising edge to defeat his upstart Democratic rival, Cynthia Nixon.
snippet: Gov. Andrew Cuomo sought to use the power of incumbency and a huge fund-raising edge to defeat his upstart Democratic rival, Cynthia Nixon.
lead_paragraph: Recriminations over a bridge opening. A false flier with a mysterious author. A cinnamon raisin bagel with cream cheese, lox and capers.

headline_main: Classical Fall Preview: Debuts, Premieres, a New Philharmonic Maestro

abstract: Grand farewells (Elton John, Paul Simon), anticipated returns (Alessia Cara, Twenty One Pilots) and buzzy emerging artists (Jessie Reyez, gnash) are coming in the new season.
snippet: Grand farewells (Elton John, Paul Simon), anticipated returns (Alessia Cara, Twenty One Pilots) and buzzy emerging artists (Jessie Reyez, gnash) are coming in the new season.
lead_paragraph: This fall’s music calendar will feature farewells, anticipated returns and emerging artists. Dates are subject to change. You can listen to a playlist of songs on Spotify from the fall preview.
